Interface CircularBufferInterface

public interface CircularBufferInterface
A buffer of fixed capacity that holds Integer objects.

    • toString

      String toString()
      Returns a string showing the contents of this buffer and indicating which end is the front and which end is the rear. The rear of the buffer is on the left (indicated by the single letter R) and the front of the buffer is on the right (indicated by the single letter F). The buffer items are surrounded by square brackets and are separated by a comma and a space. Here are some examples: An empty buffer R [] F After adding 1 R [1] F After adding 2 R [2, 1] F After adding 3 R [3, 2, 1] F After removing R [3, 2] F After removing R [3] F After removing R [] F
      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
      A string representation of this circular buffer
